23:{"_type":"issue","id":"kernel-of-truth-utq","title":"FABLE (first-wave PRIORITY): optimal-resource-usage plan — work taxonomy + architecture reuse + cross-experiment GPU-result reuse","description":"Maintainer-designated PRIORITY (Jesse, 2026-07-09): when Fable is back online, one of its FIRST tasks is to produce a concrete OPTIMAL-RESOURCE-USAGE plan (deliverable: docs/next/resource-optimization-plan.md + integration into the research-engine framework + roles/practices). Do this EARLY — before large new experiment spend — because it optimizes all downstream work. Three required components:\n\n(1) WORK TAXONOMY (Opus vs Fable boundary, made precise). Define, with a concrete decision rubric, exactly which work is ROUTINE / non-complex and can be done by cheaper models (Opus execution) WITHOUT reducing the quality or potential of experiments, vs which is complex/creative/definitional and must stay Fable. Refine the existing Fable-designs / Opus-runs split (docs/next/opus-execution-practices.md, research-engine.md §3, .claude/agents/experiment-runner.md + kb-pipeline-runner.md) into a checklist/flowchart an agent can apply per task. Goal: maximise cheap-model throughput with zero quality loss; flag any grey zones as forks.\n\n(2) ARCHITECTURE REUSE + COMPOSITION. Identify where architectures (kernel / encoder / model components) can be RE-USED and PLUGGED TOGETHER in different combinations to test architectural permutations efficiently — where the existing work to build ONE kernel can be reused to build a SIMILAR kernel (e.g. shared basis, shared minting, shared corpora, shared adapters), and where components compose so a permutation grid is covered by a small set of reusable building blocks rather than N bespoke builds. Connect to the idea-registry slots/permutations (registry/ideas.jsonl), the architecture ladder (docs/next/architecture-ladder.md), and the kernel-variant expansion split.\n\n(3) CROSS-EXPERIMENT GPU-RESULT REUSE. Identify where LOGGED training/eval outputs from one GPU run can be REUSED across multiple experiments/analyses instead of re-running — i.e. bake in the 're-analyse before re-running' principle (the F2 -\u003e f2b lesson: gap-closure was a free re-analysis over logged data). Define a results/artifact ledger + reuse rules: which arms/checkpoints/decodes are reusable across experiments, and a gate that forces a check for an existing logged result before authorising any new GPU spend.\n\nOutput: the plan doc + concrete mechanisms (rubric, reusable-component map, results-reuse ledger + pre-spend check) folded into the engine so they are enforced, not advisory.","notes":"REFINEMENT (Jesse, 2026-07-09): do NOT frame components (2) architecture-reuse and (3) GPU-result-reuse as retroactive gates ONLY. ALSO add a PROACTIVE component (4): produce a reuse-MAXIMISING ORDERING/prioritisation of pending work — sequence experiments so broadly-reusable artefacts are produced first and shared arms/checkpoints/corpora are built once and consumed many times, rather than only checking for reuse at spend time. Opus has already done the PLANNING-STEP-NOW reconnaissance the maintainer requested: docs/next/reuse-ordering-analysis.md (SPECULATIVE/uncommitted-then-committed; Opus recon, NOT a decision) — it maps dependency edges, shared pins, logged GPU outputs, and proposes a draft wave ordering (Wave 1 zero-GPU: l3a-parse/a5-nl/g5/g4+build d-ax; then POST-F2-INFRA decision; then e9-full→e9-c shared-producer-first; efficiency f-track; f7 last consuming survivors' decodes; family-h0→a-h0). Fable OWNS validating/rejecting/re-deriving this ordering and every 'reuse is licensed' call — esp. the load-bearing honesty question (§5): whether pre-registration discipline permits an experiment to consume another record's logged per-item decodes as its own arm output WITHOUT a fresh run (f2b was a replication, not pure reuse). Decide whether this folds into the backlog L-score (research-engine.md §2.7) or stands as a separate ordering.\nREUSE-PERMISSION DEFERRED (maintainer, 2026-07-09). Two cross-vendor Codex audits of the confirmatory logged-result-reuse ruling: audit-1 CONFIRM_WITH_CONDITIONS (2 criticals), revision-1 closed RC-8/RC-5/ASM, re-audit-2 REFUTE (4 criticals remained, enforcement weaker than prose; RC-7 cosmetic-in-code). Maintainer chose DEFER over revision-2: at ~$1/GPU-run the ~$1/run saving does not justify the integrity surface. LIVE: restrictive gate + fail-closed interlock + reuse_overrides + exploratory-quarantine. DEFERRED: reused_from consumption (fail-closed, no ratification file). Plan components (1)(2)(4) unaffected. Audit trail: registry/audits/resource-optimization-plan/{1-design-audit-codex,2-design-reaudit-codex}.json. This closes the P0 plan deliverable EXCEPT the deferred reuse sub-feature.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeswrsolidserver@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-07-09T13:43:43Z","created_by":"Jesse Wright","updated_at":"2026-07-09T15:40:33Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
24:{"_type":"issue","id":"kernel-of-truth-99a","title":"Kernel construction methodology: how should canonical concept representations actually be built?","description":"@jeswr (2026-07-07) stepped back from the identity/reconciliation question to the FOUNDATIONAL one: is LLM-generation (Haiku emitting NSM explications) even the right way to construct the kernel? Wikipedia-sourcing was 'a whim'. Candidate alternatives to research + test: (a) LLM-generated NSM explications (current); (b) DICTIONARY-GRAPH + convergence — turn each dictionary definition into relations, run a convergence algorithm to a fixpoint (mirrors the published 'grounding kernel' / minimum-grounding-set work of Vincent-Lamarre/Masse/Harnad 'The Latent Structure of Dictionaries', and Formal Concept Analysis); (c) EXTRACT FROM MODEL INTERNALS — 'deconstruct a local model so its output layer matches the construction we want' (SAE/dictionary-learning/interp; connects to this project's E8 kernel\u003c-\u003eSAE alignment result); (d) principled hybrids. Concern: an LLM 'just spits out what it thinks things should be like' — may be circular/ungrounded/non-canonical.","design":"Deep-research workflow w7tu4h3kr (5 Fable angles + synthesis): decompositional-semantics theory (is a canonical primitive basis real? NSM vs Fodor's atomism); dictionary-graphs/grounding-kernels (Harnad et al; FCA); symbol-grounding/circularity (Harnad SGP; distributional vs decompositional; is a definition-only kernel grounded?); model-internal extraction (SAE/monosemanticity/linear-rep; canonical? deterministic? training-free?); LLM-generator critique (proposer-then-verified vs source-of-truth; determinism from a stochastic generator). Deliverable: theory-grounded recommendation + honest uncertainty map + a SEQUENCED experimental programme (cheapest/most-decision-relevant first) to empirically discriminate the approaches. E10-fix (order-invariance of reconciliation) becomes ONE rung, downstream of choosing the substrate.","acceptance_criteria":"1) Theory-grounded recommended construction approach (or principled hybrid) with reasoning. 2) Explicit uncertainty map (settled-by-literature vs open-empirical vs philosophical). 3) A proper sequenced set of experiments, each with question/method/pass-fail/cost/decision-unblocked. 4) Clear verdict on whether LLM-generation is legitimate as a verified-proposer vs circular as source-of-truth.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-07-07T20:16:22Z","created_by":"ec2-user","updated_at":"2026-07-07T20:16:22Z","dependency_count":0,"dependent_count":0,"comment_count":0}
